x=\tan\left(\theta\right)
 \int_{0}^{1}\left(1 - x^{2}\right)^n\,{\rm d}x ={1 \over \sqrt 2} \int_{0}^{\pi/2} \cos^{n+1}\left(\theta\right)\,{\rm d}\theta\,, \qquad\Re\left(n\right) > -2 
\sin^2\theta + \cos^2\theta = 1
1 - \sin^2 \theta = \cos^2 \theta
1 - \sin^2\theta
x = \sin\theta
\begin{align} \int_0^1 (1 - x^2)^n dx &= \int_0^{\pi/2}(1 - \sin^2\theta)^n\cos\theta d\theta \\ &= \int_0^{\pi/2} \cos^{n+1}\theta d\theta, \end{align}
